69 &= 1.5a + 800b, \\
69 &= 1.2a + 1100b.
\end{align*} 2. Subtracting the second equation from the first yields $$0=0.3a-300b.$$ From this, we deduce that $$a=10^3b.$$ Substituting this into the equation $$69=1.5a+800b$$ allows us to solve for $b$: \begin{align*}
69&=1.5\cdot 1000b+800b\\
&=2000b+800b=2800b,
\end{align*}so $b=\frac{69}{2800}.$ Then we calculate $a$ with our knowledge of $b$: \begin{align*}
a=1000b=1000\cdot\frac{69}{2800}=24.5.
\end{align*} Therefore, the model predicts that it will take $(4.2)(24.5)+(4000)(\frac{69}{2800})=\boxed{\textbf{(C)}\; 252}$ minutes to complete the hike. The answer is C.
